Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createSnapshot(25.10)                                    createSnapshot(25.10)

Name
       createSnapshot  -  Creates  snapshots of the design for all three views
       (Floorplan, Amoeba, and Placement) at any stage of the design flow

Syntax
       createSnapshot

       [-help]

       -dir <string>

       -name <string>

       [-overwrite]

       Creates snapshots of the design for all three views (Floorplan, Amoeba,
       and Placement) at any stage of the design flow. The command creates GIF
       images, for all the design views, on the same scale as can be  seen  in
       the  software.  It can also save QoR parameters like WNS,TNS, Placement
       Overlap, and Congestion at any stage of the design flow. Once the snap-
       shot is created, you can view it using viewSnapshot.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each createSnapshot parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man createSnapshot.

       -dir <string>
              Specifies the directory in which you want to save the snapshot.

       -name <string>
              Specifies the name of snapshot and the files  will  be  created,
              like ss_string_view.gif for all three views.

       -overwrite
              Overwrites the existing snapshot with new one.

       Note: This command will not work in the -nowin mode.

Examples
              * The following command will create a design snapshot in the di-
                rectory  /work/user1.  Before  creating  the snapshot, it will
                create the following files:

                     * ss_cts.fplan.gif for floorplan view

                     * ss_cts.amoeba.gif for amoeba view

                     * ss_cts.place.gif for place view

                       createSnapshot -dir /work/user1 -name cts

              * The following command will create a snapshot  under  the  name
                cts.  If there exists a snapshot under this name in the direc-
                tory /work/user1, it will overwrite it.

                createSnapshot -dir /work/user1 -name cts -overwrite

